Cape Town - A Brazilian woman who was arrested earlier this week after she was allegedly found with 2.7kg of cocaine and 200g of heroin worth R870 000 hidden inside her shoes and luggage at Cape Town International Airport will be applying for bail. Tania Cavalcante Amarante, 28, made her first appearance at the Bellville Magistrate’s Court this morning. Amarante’s case has been postponed to March 3 for her formal bail application proceedings. The Hawks’ Zinzi Hani explained: “Tania Cavalcante Amarante, 28, appeared today in Bellville Magistrate’s Court. The matter has been remanded to March 3 for bail information. The accused remains in custody.” The arrest comes after an operation led by the Hawks and the SA Narcotics Enforcement Bureau, together with Crime Intelligence and Customs and Sars. The woman had arrived from Sao Paulo, Brazil and travelled via Qatar Airways. Weekend Argus